homePage.aboutText:
Grew up in Austin's blues scene, sneaking into Antone's to hear the legends. Now based in Portland, bringing that same raw energy to the Pacific Northwest.

Third place out of 400 bands at the 2017 International Blues Competition in Memphis. Berklee College of Music, magna cum laude. Twenty years teaching experience.

Not just a musician—builds custom tube amps, creates visual art, and keeps the blues alive through teaching and performing.
homePage.albumDescription: Collaboration with Anthony Pausic (drums). Blending blues traditions with guitar tones from heavier influences like doom and stoner-rock. Raw, authentic, and distinctly Pacific Northwest.
homePage.ctaLessonsText: Twenty years teaching experience. Berklee College of Music, magna cum laude. Build solid foundations in blues techniques, theory, and improvisation.
homePage.heroSubheading: Gritty Texas Blues meets the heart of the Pacific Northwest

learningItems.description: Authentic phrasing, bending, vibrato, and the feel that makes blues come alive. Learn from someone who grew up in the tradition.
learningItems.title: Blues Techniques

learningItems.description: Western harmony fundamentals that work across all genres. Functional understanding, not just memorized rules.
learningItems.title: Music Theory

learningItems.description: Build vocabulary, develop your ear, and learn to express yourself spontaneously. From simple blues licks to complex solos.
learningItems.title: Improvisation

learningItems.description: Songwriting techniques and arranging skills. Create original material with intention and purpose.
learningItems.title: Composition

learningItems.description: Recognize intervals, chords, and progressions by ear. Transcribe solos, internalize what you hear.
learningItems.title: Ear Training

learningItems.description: Tone, touch, and technique. The physical aspects of playing that bring your musical ideas to life.
learningItems.title: Guitar Craft

lessonsPage.philosophyText:
We start with foundational concepts and build through Western harmony. You'll develop a cross-instrumental understanding that transcends your specific instrument.

Solid musical foundations first. Then we explore blues phrasing, improvisation, composition, and the theory that connects it all.

The goal: intentionality in your artistic creation. Understanding why something works, not just how to play it.

contactPage.heroSubheading:
(I will really get back to you.)

Booking inquiries, lesson scheduling, collaborations, or just to say hello.

setlistPage.ctaText: Learn authentic blues guitar with professional instruction. From foundational techniques to advanced improvisation—build your blues vocabulary with a Berklee graduate and working musician.
setlistPage.introText: A carefully curated collection from Chicago electric to Texas roadhouse. Each song arranged in its authentic key for maximum soul. These are the classics that shaped the blues.
